Package: att-gateway-check
Version: 0.1.0
Architecture: all
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Gardner <gardner@homelab>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.11), python3-requests, python3-urllib3, python3-bs4, systemd
Description: AT&T BGW320-500 Gateway Configuration Manager
 Monitors, backs up, and restores configuration on AT&T residential
 gateways. Automatically detects and fixes configuration changes caused
 by firmware updates.
 .
 Features:
  - Firmware version detection and adaptation
  - Continuous monitoring with auto-fix (every 30 minutes)
  - Comprehensive configuration backups
  - Automatic page discovery
  - Selective or full restore capability
  - Backup retention management
  - Systemd timer integration
 .
 The tool runs as a systemd service and automatically monitors your
 gateway configuration, fixing any changes made by AT&T firmware updates.
Homepage: https://github.com/permittivity2/att-home-router-automation
